button.buyMore.description: Button text allowing the user to purchase more credits.

button.uploadReferences.description: Button text allowing the user to upload references.

button.success.description: Button text indicating the operation was successful.

button.generating.description: Button text that indicates the operation is in progress

button.failed.description: Button text that indicates the operation has failed

button.download.description: Button text that allows the user to download the results

button.fast.description: Button text that allows the user to set 'fast mode' to quickly generate the image, must be translated to 'Fast Mode'

button.relax.description: Button text that allows the user to set 'slow mode' to relax the image generation, must be translated to 'Slow Mode'

button.turbo.description: Button text that allows the user to set 'turbo mode' to enhance image generation speed, must be translated to 'Turbo Mode'

button.more.description: Button text that allows the user to view more options

button.generate.description: Button text that allows the user to generate an image

button.history.description: Button text that allows the user to view the history of generated images

button.generateNew.description: Button text that allows the user to create a new image

field.finalPrompt.description: The final prompt used to generate the image

field.elements.description: The painting style used to generate the image

field.traceId.description: The trace ID used to track the image generation request, do not translate, keep as 'Trace ID'

description.aspect.message: --aspect, changes the aspect ratio of the generated image, the default depends on the model and mode
description.aspect.description: Description of the aspect ratio parameter

description.chaos.message: --chaos, adjusts the degree of variation in the generated image; the higher the number, the more unique and unexpected the generated images become, ranging from 0-100, default is 1

description.fast.message: Ignores current settings, runs a single generation task in 'fast mode', no default value

description.iw.message: --iw, sets the importance of the image prompt relative to the text prompt during generation, ranging from 0-2, default is 1

description.no.message: --no, indicates the generation system to attempt to exclude certain elements, e.g., '--no plants' will try to generate an image without plants, no default value
description.no.description: Description of the exclusion parameter, translate to 'Exclude'

description.quality.message: --quality, sets the quality and rendering time of the generated image, ranging from .25, .5, or 1, default is 1

description.random.message: Adds random basic style codes to the prompt; various lengths of random style effects can be obtained using '--style random-16', '--style random-64', or '--style random-128', no default value

description.relax.message: Overrides current settings, runs a single task in 'slow mode', no default value

description.repeat.message: --repeat, creates multiple tasks from a single prompt, ranging from 1-40, default is 1

description.seed.message: --seed, the initial visual noise for generating the image, ranging from 0-4294967295, default is randomly generated

description.stop.message: --stop, stops the task at any stage of the generation process, ranging from 10-100, default is 100 (i.e., fully generated)

description.style.message: --style, switches between different versions or styles of Midjourney or Niji models, such as raw, cute, expressive, original, scenic; the default depends on the model and mode

description.stylize.message: --stylize, adjusts the intensity of the Midjourney default aesthetic style applied in the generation task, ranging from 0-1000, default is 100

description.tile.message: --tile, generates images that can be used to create seamless tiles, no default value

description.turbo.message: Overrides current settings, runs a single task in 'turbo mode', no default value

description.weird.message: --weird, explore unusual aesthetic styles with an experimental nature, range from 0-3000, default is 0

description.translation.message: Enable automatic translation during the generation process, non-Chinese content will be automatically translated into Midjourney's English input

description.imageWeight.message: --iw, adjust the weight of the image prompt relative to the text prompt, range from 0-2, default is 1
description.imageWeight.description: Description of the image weight parameter

description.niji.message: --niji, when enabled, the generated images will use the Niji model to create anime-style images

description.uploadReferences.message: Upload images as references for generation, supports a maximum of 5 images. If more than 1 image is uploaded, they will be automatically merged
description.uploadReferences.description: Description of the upload references parameter

description.raw.message: --raw, when enabled, the generated images will use the Midjourney model to create raw style images

description.prompt.message: Enter the command, if additional parameters are added, they will override the default preset parameters, for example, adding '--stylize 200' will force the final command to use '--stylize 200'

model.general.description: Model name for general image generation

model.niji.description: Model name for anime style image generation, please do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.model.description: Name of the model; model is a term used in machine learning for generating images

name.aspect.description: Name of the aspect ratio parameter

name.chaos.description: Name of the chaos parameter, translate as 'Chaos Level'

name.fast.description: Name of the fast mode for quick image generation, translate as 'Fast Mode'

name.nijiStyle.description: Name of the nijiStyle parameter, please do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.imageWeight.description: Name of the image weight parameter

name.no.description: Name of the exclude parameter, used to exclude specific elements, translate as 'Exclude'

name.quality.description: Name of the quality parameter, used to set the quality of generated images

name.mode.description: Name of the speed parameter, used to set the speed of image generation

name.random.description: Name of the random parameter, used to add random style effects

name.relax.description: Name of the relax mode for generating images in 'slow mode', translate as 'Slow Mode'

name.repeat.description: Name of the repeat parameter, used to create multiple tasks from a single prompt

name.seed.description: Name of the seed parameter, used to set the initial visual noise

name.stop.description: Name of the stop parameter, used to stop the task at any stage

name.style.description: Name of the style parameter, used to switch between different versions or styles of the model

name.stylize.description: Name of the stylize parameter, used to adjust the strength of the default aesthetic style

name.tile.description: Name of the tile parameter, used to generate images that can be tiled

name.turbo.description: Name of the turbo mode for generating images in 'turbo mode', translate as 'Turbo Mode'

name.weird.description: Name of the weirdness parameter, used to explore unusual aesthetic styles, translate as 'Weirdness Level'

name.translation.description: Name of the translation parameter, used to enable automatic translation during generation

name.advanced.description: Name of the advanced mode, used to enable advanced mode

name.niji.description: Name of the niji parameter, used to enable the Niji model, please do not translate, keep as 'Niji'

name.ignore.description: Name of the ignore parameter, used to ignore certain elements

name.prompt.description: Name of the prompt parameter, used to input drawing instructions

name.raw.description: Name of the raw parameter, used to enable the Midjourney model
